# 5. Ler resultado pequeno com boto3

Bom para testes que retornam poucas linhas.

```python
def get_athena_results(query_execution_id: str) -> list[dict]:
    paginator = athena.get_paginator("get_query_results")

    rows = []

    for page in paginator.paginate(QueryExecutionId=query_execution_id):
        result_rows = page["ResultSet"]["Rows"]

        if not rows:
            header = [
                col.get("VarCharValue")
                for col in result_rows[0]["Data"]
            ]
            data_rows = result_rows[1:]
        else:
            data_rows = result_rows

        for row in data_rows:
            values = [
                col.get("VarCharValue")
                for col in row["Data"]
            ]
            rows.append(dict(zip(header, values)))

    return rows
```

